verbose_text: Unlike the other PKM2 interactors HPV16-E7, which inhibits PKM2 tetramerization by acetylating PKM2 at K433 XREF_BIBR, and CD44, which inhibits PKM2 tetramerization by phosphorylating PKM2 at Tyr105 XREF_BIBR, TBC1D8 does not change the acetylation or phosphorylation levels of PKM2.
evidence: CD44, which inhibits PKM2 tetramerization by phosphorylating PKM2 at Tyr105
